11/12/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Mircea Geoana was re-elected on Sunday (December 10th) as leader of the main opposition Social Democratic Party (PSD). The former foreign minister won a new four-year term, beating out PSD Bucharest branch chairman Sorin Oprescu. Afterwards, Geoana pledged to lead the party to victory during the 2008 general elections. 
In other news, Dan Motreanu was sworn in on Friday as the new agriculture minister, succeeding Gheorghe Flutur in the post. (Ziua - 11/12/06; Mediafax - 10/12/06; Romanian Government website, Rompres - 08/12/06)
